---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import CodeBlock from '../../../components/CodeBlock.astro';
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Accordion - Red Elements"
  description="A vertically stacked set of interactive headings that each reveal a section of content."
>
  <div class="space-y-6">
    <div>
      <h1 class="scroll-m-20 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">Accordion</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-[color:light-dark(var(--color-muted-foreground),var(--color-muted-foreground-dark))] mt-2">
        A vertically stacked set of interactive headings that each reveal a section of content.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="scroll-m-20 border-b pb-2 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
        Demo
      </h2>
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-[color:light-dark(var(--color-border),var(--color-border-dark))] p-6">
        <accordion-root class="w-full">
          <accordion-item value="item-1" class="border-b border-[color:light-dark(var(--color-border),var(--color-border-dark))]">
            <accordion-header>
              <accordion-trigger class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-4 font-medium transition-all hover:underline [&[data-state=open]>svg]:rotate-180">
                Is it accessible?
                <svg class="h-4 w-4 shrink-0 transition-transform duration-200" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
                </svg>
              </accordion-trigger>
            </accordion-header>
            <accordion-content class="overflow-hidden text-sm transition-all data-[state=closed]:animate-accordion-up data-[state=open]:animate-accordion-down">
              <div class="pb-4 pt-0">
                Yes. It adheres to the WAI-ARIA design pattern.
              </div>
            </accordion-content>
          </accordion-item>

          <accordion-item value="item-2" class="border-b border-[color:light-dark(var(--color-border),var(--color-border-dark))]">
            <accordion-header>
              <accordion-trigger class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-4 font-medium transition-all hover:underline [&[data-state=open]>svg]:rotate-180">
                Is it unstyled?
                <svg class="h-4 w-4 shrink-0 transition-transform duration-200" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
                </svg>
              </accordion-trigger>
            </accordion-header>
            <accordion-content class="overflow-hidden text-sm transition-all data-[state=closed]:animate-accordion-up data-[state=open]:animate-accordion-down">
              <div class="pb-4 pt-0">
                Yes. It's unstyled by default, giving you full control over the styling.
              </div>
            </accordion-content>
          </accordion-item>

          <accordion-item value="item-3" class="border-b border-[color:light-dark(var(--color-border),var(--color-border-dark))]">
            <accordion-header>
              <accordion-trigger class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-4 font-medium transition-all hover:underline [&[data-state=open]>svg]:rotate-180">
                Can it be animated?
                <svg class="h-4 w-4 shrink-0 transition-transform duration-200" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
                </svg>
              </accordion-trigger>
            </accordion-header>
            <accordion-content class="overflow-hidden text-sm transition-all data-[state=closed]:animate-accordion-up data-[state=open]:animate-accordion-down">
              <div class="pb-4 pt-0">
                Yes! You can animate it with CSS transitions or any animation library.
              </div>
            </accordion-content>
          </accordion-item>
        </accordion-root>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="scroll-m-20 border-b pb-2 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
        Installation
      </h2>
      <tabs-root default-value="npm" class="w-full">
        <tabs-list class="inline-flex h-10 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-[color:light-dark(var(--color-muted),var(--color-muted-dark))] p-1 text-[color:light-dark(var(--color-muted-foreground),var(--color-muted-foreground-dark))]">
          <tab-trigger value="npm" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center whitespace-nowrap rounded-sm px-3 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium transition-all cursor-pointer data-[state=active]:bg-[color:light-dark(var(--color-background),var(--color-background-dark))] data-[state=active]:text-[color:light-dark(var(--color-foreground),var(--color-foreground-dark))] data-[state=active]:shadow-sm">
            npm
          </tab-trigger>
          <tab-trigger value="pnpm" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center whitespace-nowrap rounded-sm px-3 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium transition-all cursor-pointer data-[state=active]:bg-[color:light-dark(var(--color-background),var(--color-background-dark))] data-[state=active]:text-[color:light-dark(var(--color-foreground),var(--color-foreground-dark))] data-[state=active]:shadow-sm">
            pnpm
          </tab-trigger>
          <tab-trigger value="yarn" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center whitespace-nowrap rounded-sm px-3 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium transition-all cursor-pointer data-[state=active]:bg-[color:light-dark(var(--color-background),var(--color-background-dark))] data-[state=active]:text-[color:light-dark(var(--color-foreground),var(--color-foreground-dark))] data-[state=active]:shadow-sm">
            yarn
          </tab-trigger>
          <tab-trigger value="bun" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center whitespace-nowrap rounded-sm px-3 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium transition-all cursor-pointer data-[state=active]:bg-[color:light-dark(var(--color-background),var(--color-background-dark))] data-[state=active]:text-[color:light-dark(var(--color-foreground),var(--color-foreground-dark))] data-[state=active]:shadow-sm">
            bun
          </tab-trigger>
        </tabs-list>
        <tab-content value="npm" class="mt-4">
          <CodeBlock
            code="npm install @red-elements/accordion"
            lang="bash"
          />
        </tab-content>
        <tab-content value="pnpm" class="mt-4">
          <CodeBlock
            code="pnpm add @red-elements/accordion"
            lang="bash"
          />
        </tab-content>
        <tab-content value="yarn" class="mt-4">
          <CodeBlock
            code="yarn add @red-elements/accordion"
            lang="bash"
          />
        </tab-content>
        <tab-content value="bun" class="mt-4">
          <CodeBlock
            code="bun add @red-elements/accordion"
            lang="bash"
          />
        </tab-content>
      </tabs-root>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="scroll-m-20 border-b pb-2 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
        Usage
      </h2>

      <tabs-root default-value="html" class="w-full">
        <tabs-list class="inline-flex h-10 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-[color:light-dark(var(--color-muted),var(--color-muted-dark))] p-1 text-[color:light-dark(var(--color-muted-foreground),var(--color-muted-foreground-dark))]">
          <tab-trigger value="html" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center whitespace-nowrap rounded-sm px-3 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium transition-all cursor-pointer data-[state=active]:bg-[color:light-dark(var(--color-background),var(--color-background-dark))] data-[state=active]:text-[color:light-dark(var(--color-foreground),var(--color-foreground-dark))] data-[state=active]:shadow-sm">
            HTML/JS
          </tab-trigger>
          <tab-trigger value="react" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center whitespace-nowrap rounded-sm px-3 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium transition-all cursor-pointer data-[state=active]:bg-[color:light-dark(var(--color-background),var(--color-background-dark))] data-[state=active]:text-[color:light-dark(var(--color-foreground),var(--color-foreground-dark))] data-[state=active]:shadow-sm">
            React
          </tab-trigger>
          <tab-trigger value="vue" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center whitespace-nowrap rounded-sm px-3 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium transition-all cursor-pointer data-[state=active]:bg-[color:light-dark(var(--color-background),var(--color-background-dark))] data-[state=active]:text-[color:light-dark(var(--color-foreground),var(--color-foreground-dark))] data-[state=active]:shadow-sm">
            Vue
          </tab-trigger>
          <tab-trigger value="svelte" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center whitespace-nowrap rounded-sm px-3 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium transition-all cursor-pointer data-[state=active]:bg-[color:light-dark(var(--color-background),var(--color-background-dark))] data-[state=active]:text-[color:light-dark(var(--color-foreground),var(--color-foreground-dark))] data-[state=active]:shadow-sm">
            Svelte
          </tab-trigger>
          <tab-trigger value="angular" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center whitespace-nowrap rounded-sm px-3 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium transition-all cursor-pointer data-[state=active]:bg-[color:light-dark(var(--color-background),var(--color-background-dark))] data-[state=active]:text-[color:light-dark(var(--color-foreground),var(--color-foreground-dark))] data-[state=active]:shadow-sm">
            Angular
          </tab-trigger>
        </tabs-list>
        <tab-content value="html" class="mt-4">
          <CodeBlock
            code={`import '@red-elements/accordion';

// Use directly in your HTML
<accordion-root>
  <accordion-item value="item-1">
    <accordion-header>
      <accordion-trigger>
        Is it accessible?
      </accordion-trigger>
    </accordion-header>
    <accordion-content>
      <div>Yes. It adheres to the WAI-ARIA design pattern.</div>
    </accordion-content>
  </accordion-item>

  <accordion-item value="item-2">
    <accordion-header>
      <accordion-trigger>
        Is it unstyled?
      </accordion-trigger>
    </accordion-header>
    <accordion-content>
      <div>Yes. It's unstyled by default.</div>
    </accordion-content>
  </accordion-item>
</accordion-root>`}
            lang="javascript"
          />
        </tab-content>

        <tab-content value="react" class="mt-4">
          <CodeBlock
            code={`import {
  AccordionRoot,
  AccordionItem,
  AccordionHeader,
  AccordionTrigger,
  AccordionContent
} from '@red-elements/accordion';

export function AccordionDemo() {
  return (
    <AccordionRoot>
      <AccordionItem value="item-1">
        <AccordionHeader>
          <AccordionTrigger>Is it accessible?</AccordionTrigger>
        </AccordionHeader>
        <AccordionContent>
          <div>Yes. It adheres to the WAI-ARIA design pattern.</div>
        </AccordionContent>
      </AccordionItem>

      <AccordionItem value="item-2">
        <AccordionHeader>
          <AccordionTrigger>Is it unstyled?</AccordionTrigger>
        </AccordionHeader>
        <AccordionContent>
          <div>Yes. It's unstyled by default.</div>
        </AccordionContent>
      </AccordionItem>
    </AccordionRoot>
  );
}`}
            lang="tsx"
          />
        </tab-content>

        <tab-content value="vue" class="mt-4">
          <CodeBlock
            code={`<script setup>
import '@red-elements/accordion';
</script>

<template>
  <accordion-root>
    <accordion-item value="item-1">
      <accordion-header>
        <accordion-trigger>Is it accessible?</accordion-trigger>
      </accordion-header>
      <accordion-content>
        <div>Yes. It adheres to the WAI-ARIA design pattern.</div>
      </accordion-content>
    </accordion-item>

    <accordion-item value="item-2">
      <accordion-header>
        <accordion-trigger>Is it unstyled?</accordion-trigger>
      </accordion-header>
      <accordion-content>
        <div>Yes. It's unstyled by default.</div>
      </accordion-content>
    </accordion-item>
  </accordion-root>
</template>`}
            lang="vue"
          />
        </tab-content>

        <tab-content value="svelte" class="mt-4">
          <CodeBlock
            code={`<script>
  import '@red-elements/accordion';
</script>

<accordion-root>
  <accordion-item value="item-1">
    <accordion-header>
      <accordion-trigger>Is it accessible?</accordion-trigger>
    </accordion-header>
    <accordion-content>
      <div>Yes. It adheres to the WAI-ARIA design pattern.</div>
    </accordion-content>
  </accordion-item>

  <accordion-item value="item-2">
    <accordion-header>
      <accordion-trigger>Is it unstyled?</accordion-trigger>
    </accordion-header>
    <accordion-content>
      <div>Yes. It's unstyled by default.</div>
    </accordion-content>
  </accordion-item>
</accordion-root>`}
            lang="svelte"
          />
        </tab-content>

        <tab-content value="angular" class="mt-4">
          <CodeBlock
            code={`// app.component.ts
import { Component } from '@angular/core';
import '@red-elements/accordion';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  template: \`
    <accordion-root>
      <accordion-item value="item-1">
        <accordion-header>
          <accordion-trigger>Is it accessible?</accordion-trigger>
        </accordion-header>
        <accordion-content>
          <div>Yes. It adheres to the WAI-ARIA design pattern.</div>
        </accordion-content>
      </accordion-item>

      <accordion-item value="item-2">
        <accordion-header>
          <accordion-trigger>Is it unstyled?</accordion-trigger>
        </accordion-header>
        <accordion-content>
          <div>Yes. It's unstyled by default.</div>
        </accordion-content>
      </accordion-item>
    </accordion-root>
  \`
})
export class AppComponent {}`}
            lang="typescript"
          />
        </tab-content>
      </tabs-root>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="scroll-m-20 border-b pb-2 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
        API Reference
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h3 class="scroll-m-20 text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
          AccordionRoot
        </h3>
        <p class="leading-7">
          The root component that manages accordion state.
        </p>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full border-collapse border border-[color:light-dark(var(--color-border),var(--color-border-dark))]">
            <thead>
              <tr class="bg-[color:light-dark(var(--color-muted),var(--color-muted-dark))]">
                <th class="border border-[color:light-dark(var(--color-border),var(--color-border-dark))] px-4 py-2 text-left">Prop</th>
                <th class="border border-[color:light-dark(var(--color-border),var(--color-border-dark))] px-4 py-2 text-left">Type</th>
                <th class="border border-[color:light-dark(var(--color-border),var(--color-border-dark))] px-4 py-2 text-left">Default</th>
                <th class="border border-[color:light-dark(var(--color-border),var(--color-border-dark))] px-4 py-2 text-left">Description</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-[color:light-dark(var(--color-border),var(--color-border-dark))] px-4 py-2"><code>type</code></td>
                <td class="border border-[color:light-dark(var(--color-border),var(--color-border-dark))] px-4 py-2">"single" | "multiple"</td>
                <td class="border border-[color:light-dark(var(--color-border),var(--color-border-dark))] px-4 py-2">"single"</td>
                <td class="border border-[color:light-dark(var(--color-border),var(--color-border-dark))] px-4 py-2">Whether multiple items can be open at once</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-[color:light-dark(var(--color-border),var(--color-border-dark))] px-4 py-2"><code>collapsible</code></td>
                <td class="border border-[color:light-dark(var(--color-border),var(--color-border-dark))] px-4 py-2">boolean</td>
                <td class="border border-[color:light-dark(var(--color-border),var(--color-border-dark))] px-4 py-2">false</td>
                <td class="border border-[color:light-dark(var(--color-border),var(--color-border-dark))] px-4 py-2">Whether an item can be collapsed after being opened</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-[color:light-dark(var(--color-border),var(--color-border-dark))] px-4 py-2"><code>disabled</code></td>
                <td class="border border-[color:light-dark(var(--color-border),var(--color-border-dark))] px-4 py-2">boolean</td>
                <td class="border border-[color:light-dark(var(--color-border),var(--color-border-dark))] px-4 py-2">false</td>
                <td class="border border-[color:light-dark(var(--color-border),var(--color-border-dark))] px-4 py-2">When true, prevents user interaction</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h3 class="scroll-m-20 text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
          Other Components
        </h3>
        <ul class="ml-6 list-disc space-y-2">
          <li><code>AccordionItem</code> - Contains all the parts of a collapsible section</li>
          <li><code>AccordionHeader</code> - Wraps an AccordionTrigger</li>
          <li><code>AccordionTrigger</code> - Toggles the collapsed state</li>
          <li><code>AccordionContent</code> - The collapsible content</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="scroll-m-20 border-b pb-2 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
        Data Attributes
      </h2>
      <p class="leading-7">
        The following data attributes are automatically applied for styling:
      </p>
      <ul class="ml-6 list-disc space-y-2">
        <li><code>data-state</code> - "open" | "closed" on AccordionItem, AccordionTrigger, and AccordionContent</li>
        <li><code>data-disabled</code> - Present when the item is disabled</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="scroll-m-20 border-b pb-2 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
        Accessibility
      </h2>
      <p class="leading-7">
        The accordion component follows WAI-ARIA guidelines:
      </p>
      <ul class="ml-6 list-disc space-y-2">
        <li class="leading-7">Full keyboard navigation support</li>
        <li class="leading-7">Proper ARIA attributes for screen readers</li>
        <li class="leading-7">Focus management</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
